The article discusses President Donald Trump's commitment to the NATO Alliance and his efforts to strengthen it. President Trump is working with NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg towards a successful NATO Summit in July 2018. He has prioritized working with NATO Allies to ensure they meet their defense spending commitments, which is in the interest of all NATO members. NATO countries are also taking steps to enhance collective defense, deter Russia, fight terrorism, and defend NATO territory. Additionally, NATO is increasing its contributions to the global fight against terrorism, as urged by President Trump.